      "writtenOn": "2015-09-17T08:06:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually this needs a little clarification, i.e. \u0027engine\u0027 is what\u0027s really performs the emulation at runtime, while \u0027glue\u0027 is the plumbing between a specific engine (QEMU1 or QEMU2) and AndroidEmu. I\u0027ll modify the doc to make this clear.",
