    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "843d32a1_f8d2be91",
        "filename": "docs/ANDROID-EMULATION-LIBRARY.TXT",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 112,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079424
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-16T22:38:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is a great example showing the value to let the library having the same interface as QEMU1. Thanks!\n\nJust curious, are there many cases where QEMU1 and QEMU2 have different interfaces? If so, how should we design the lib\u0027s interface? Being closer to QEMU1 can help us move generic code out of android-qemu1/ sooner, while being closer to QEMU2 is likely leading to a cleaner code base in the long run. What do you think?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 112,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 112,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "d6ef5cb13b499aa1f5114921b0c246d100a9e0a9",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0984fbca_428952a9",
        "filename": "docs/ANDROID-EMULATION-LIBRARY.TXT",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 112,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-17T08:06:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, there are significant differences between QEMU1 and QEMU2 internals, the larger ones being how virtual devices are actually declared / initialized / run. However, the interfaces we\u0027re going to deal with to connect with AndroidEmu should not be too problematic.",
      "parentUuid": "843d32a1_f8d2be91",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 112,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 112,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "d6ef5cb13b499aa1f5114921b0c246d100a9e0a9",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "64383eb1_56a1ea62",
        "filename": "docs/ANDROID-EMULATION-LIBRARY.TXT",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 150,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079424
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-16T22:38:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How do we know the code moving out is actually generic? Is it possible to have a policy/guide that newly moved out code should be linked against QEMU2 in a reasonable timeframe? So they are at least syntactic generic.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 150,
        "startChar": 69,
        "endLine": 150,
        "endChar": 76
      },
      "revId": "d6ef5cb13b499aa1f5114921b0c246d100a9e0a9",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e986c7d4_e143c631",
        "filename": "docs/ANDROID-EMULATION-LIBRARY.TXT",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
